comment._content: It looks like Walter Jenkinson Kaye went on to become Master of Ilkley College in Yorkshire. Born circa 1843, he passed away in 1919 and was buried with his wife, Louisa, who predeceased him in 1911. They are commemorated on the same headstone at Harlow Hill Cemetery, Harrogate, Yorkshire. www.gravestonephotos.com/public/gravedetails.php?availabl... On the 1911 census taken at the end of March, Walter Jenkinson Kaye, (aged 67 and married), was recorded as the head of the household at "Pembroke", Park View, Harrogate. He gave his profession as Retired Private School Master and was born Shipley, Yorkshire. His wife isn't recorded in the household. However there is a son and a daughter. Walter Jenkinson Kaye Junior, aged 40 and single, was working as a Private Tutor. He was born Newton-in-Bowland, Yorkshire. Edith Jane Kaye, aged 39 and single, was working as the Headmistress of a Private School. She was born Ackworth, Yorkshire.
